### =============================================================================
### Exercise 3 — Declarative Constraints
###
### One SUCCESS + one FAILURE request per constraint pattern shown in the
### workshop. The redundant siblings in `travel-constraints.cds` (Customer,
### EndDate, BookingFee, FlightPrice, Bookings.Travel @mandatory) all follow
### one of the patterns below — skim them in the source if curious.
###
### How to run:
### 1. From `xstravels/`, run `npm run update-dates` so the seed data is
###    anchored to today (±60/+90 days rolling window).
### 2. Start the app:  `cds watch`   (defaults to port 4004)
### 3. Open this file in VS Code with the "REST Client" extension installed,
###    then click "Send Request" above each block.
###
### Every request runs under user `alice` (mocked auth).
### =============================================================================

@host      = http://localhost:4004
@service   = {{host}}/odata/v4/travel
@auth      = Basic alice:

### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Helpers — discover valid seed data (the exact IDs and dates depend on when
### you ran `npm run update-dates`, so start by picking real values from these
### queries and use them in the requests below.)
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### List a couple of Travels (grab an ID + its window)
GET {{service}}/Travels?$top=3&$select=ID,BeginDate,EndDate,Currency_code,Status_code
Authorization: {{auth}}

### List a few Flights in USD within the current data window
GET {{service}}/Flights?$top=5&$select=ID,date,currency_code,price&$filter=currency_code eq 'USD'&$orderby=date asc
Authorization: {{auth}}

### List a few Flights in EUR (used for the currency-mismatch test)
GET {{service}}/Flights?$top=3&$select=ID,date,currency_code,price&$filter=currency_code eq 'EUR'
Authorization: {{auth}}

### =============================================================================
### CONSTRAINTS ON `Travels`
### =============================================================================

### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1) Description  — null check + string function
###    when Description is null                 → 'Description is required'
###    when length(trim(Description)) < 3       → 'Description is too short'
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 1a) ✅ SUCCESS — valid description
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Team offsite in Berlin",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "BookingFee":  10,
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001"
}

### 1b) ❌ FAIL — description too short  →  "Description is too short"
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "AB",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "BookingFee":  10,
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001"
}


### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2) Agency  — @mandatory shorthand + `not exists <assoc>` referential check
###    (Same shape as the `Customer` constraint — skip the near-duplicate.)
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 2a) ✅ SUCCESS — existing agency (070001 = Sunshine Travel)
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip with valid agency",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001"
}

### 2b) ❌ FAIL — Agency omitted  →  ASSERT_MANDATORY
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip without agency",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Customer_ID": "000001"
}

### 2c) ❌ FAIL — Agency ID that does not exist  →  "Agency does not exist"
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip with unknown agency",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "999999",
  "Customer_ID": "000001"
}


### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3) BeginDate / EndDate  — cross-field compare + filtered `exists` into to-many
###    when EndDate < BeginDate → ASSERT_BEGINDATE_BEFORE_ENDDATE
###                            + ASSERT_ENDDATE_AFTER_BEGINDATE  (mirror sibling)
###    Both messages are reported — one per field — via MULTIPLE_ERRORS.
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 3a) ✅ SUCCESS — BeginDate before EndDate
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip in the right order",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001"
}

### 3b) ❌ FAIL — BeginDate after EndDate
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip with dates swapped",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-15",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-10",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001"
}


### =============================================================================
### CONSTRAINTS ON `Bookings`
###
### The service has a handler that blocks creating a Booking directly via
### POST /Bookings (drafts only). Booking-level constraints are therefore
### exercised here by creating a Travel with a nested Booking (composition).
### =============================================================================

### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4) Bookings.Flight.date  — $self up to parent + `not between` range check
###    when date not between $self.Travel.BeginDate and $self.Travel.EndDate
###           → ASSERT_BOOKING_IN_TRAVEL_PERIOD
###    Also mirrored on the parent side (BeginDate/EndDate) as
###    ASSERT_BOOKINGS_IN_TRAVEL_PERIOD via a filtered-exists.
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 4a) ✅ SUCCESS — flight date inside the travel period
###     Replace the Flight_ID and Flight_date with values returned by the
###     "USD flights" helper query at the top of this file — pick one whose
###     date lies between BeginDate and EndDate of the parent Travel.
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip with in-range booking",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001",
  "Bookings": [
    { "Pos": 1,
      "Flight_ID":    "SW0067",
      "Flight_date":  "2026-08-12",
      "FlightPrice":  415,
      "Currency_code":"USD" }
  ]
}

### 4b) ❌ FAIL — flight date outside the travel period
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip with out-of-range booking",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001",
  "Bookings": [
    { "Pos": 1,
      "Flight_ID":    "SW1537",
      "Flight_date":  "2026-09-21",
      "FlightPrice":  805,
      "Currency_code":"USD" }
  ]
}


### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 5) Bookings.Currency  — child value must match the parent's
###    when Currency != Travel.Currency → ASSERT_BOOKING_CURRENCY_MATCHES_TRAVEL
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 5a) ✅ SUCCESS — same currency as the travel
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip with matching currency",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001",
  "Bookings": [
    { "Pos": 1,
      "Flight_ID":    "SW0067",
      "Flight_date":  "2026-08-12",
      "FlightPrice":  415,
      "Currency_code":"USD" }
  ]
}

### 5b) ❌ FAIL — booking currency (EUR) differs from travel currency (USD)
POST {{service}}/Travels
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "Description": "Trip with mismatched currency",
  "BeginDate":   "2026-08-10",
  "EndDate":     "2026-08-15",
  "Currency_code": "USD",
  "Agency_ID":   "070001",
  "Customer_ID": "000001",
  "Bookings": [
    { "Pos": 1,
      "Flight_ID":    "SW0067",
      "Flight_date":  "2026-08-12",
      "FlightPrice":  415,
      "Currency_code":"EUR" }
  ]
}


### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6) Bookings.BookingDate  — constraint on a child, but fires when the *parent*
###    is edited. `BookingDate` is @Core.Computed (defaults to $now, read-only
###    for clients), so the realistic way to violate this is to shrink the
###    parent Travel's window until an existing booking is orphaned.
###
###    The 3-step draft flow below is the whole point: it demonstrates that
###    constraints re-evaluate on `draftActivate` against *all* affected rows,
###    including children the client didn't touch.
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### 6a) Put an existing Travel into edit mode (draft).
###     Adjust the ID to a Travel that has bookings — Travel 1 works out of
###     the box with the seed data.
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.draftEdit
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "PreserveChanges": true }

### 6b) PATCH the draft's EndDate to before the earliest existing booking.
###     Travel 1's earliest booking sits around 2026-09-18; shrinking EndDate
###     to 2026-09-15 orphans it.
PATCH {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=false)
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "EndDate": "2026-09-15" }

### 6c) ❌ FAIL — activate the draft. The framework evaluates every affected
###     constraint and reports them together. You'll see
###     `ASSERT_NO_BOOKINGS_AFTER_TRAVEL` in the `details` array (alongside
###     the begin/end-date and travel-period constraints that also trip when
###     the window shrinks).
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=false)/TravelService.draftActivate
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}
